;field-item odd&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/all-access-tags/webinar-opportunity&quot; typeof=&quot;skos:Concept&quot; property=&quot;rdfs:label skos:prefLabel&quot; datatype=&quot;&quot;&gt;Webinar Opportunity&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot; property=&quot;content:encoded&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Join the Access &amp;amp; Diversity Collaborative for on Wednesday, March 2, 3-4 pm ET, for a free webinar, &lt;em&gt;Preparing for &lt;/em&gt;Fisher II &lt;em&gt;on Your Campus. &lt;/em&gt;The webinar will provide recommendations to help institutions prepare for the U.S. Supreme Court’s second decision in &lt;em&gt;Fisher v. University of Texas at Austin, &lt;/em&gt;which is expected by late June 2016 (though it may come sooner). Written materials will be available in advance of the webinar.&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Space is limited-- p&lt;/span&gt;lease register for the webinar here. We recommend that participants and their colleagues view the webinar together, and then apply guidance from the webinar to action planning for their own campuses. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The webinar is hosted by the College Board’s &lt;a href=&quot;https://professionals.collegeboard.org/higher-ed/access-and-diversity-collaborative&quot;&gt;Access &amp;amp; Diversity Collaborative&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.acenet.edu/Pages/default.aspx&quot;&gt;American Council on Education&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&quot;http://educationcounsel.com&quot;&gt;EducationCounsel.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
